Decreases random number of dimensions to a maximum of 3 to prevent huge tensors.  This fixes a bug where the test was not running with runs_per_test=2. Due to the random seed being fixed with runs_per_test=1 the numbers that were sampled were small enough by chance. With runs_per_test=2 a second set of tensor shapes was sampled which led to huge tensors that did not fit in memory.  PiperOrigin-RevId: 302609726

Add rasterizer_op to tensorflow_graphics pip package.  The change does the following:  - Exports BUILD files for cc targets and tests needed for rasterizer_op     -- tensorflow_graphics/rendering/opengl/BUILD     -- tensorflow_graphics/util/BUILD  - Fixes a few Bazel issues to properly set up dependencies     -- Adds headers transitively included by rasterizer op in tensorflow_graphics/third_party/tf.bzl     -- Adds empty tensorflow_graphics/third_party/BUILD     -- Adds absl as dependency in tensorflow_graphics/opensource/WORKSPACE  - Includes rasterizer_op shared library to pip package     -- Adds rasterizer op to tensorflow_graphics/rendering/opengl/__init__.py, rasterizer module can be accessed as `from tensorflow_graphics.rendering.opengl import rasterizer` from the pip package     -- Includes the shared library in tensorflow_graphics/opensource/MANIFEST.in     -- Allows including non python files in tensorflow_graphics/opensource/setup.py  - Adds CI steps for rasterizer op     -- Adds steps to build rasterizer_op.so     -- Adds script to install mesa libraries that are compatible with the standard library used for building TensorFlow at tensorflow_graphics/opensource/build_rasterizer.sh  - A few other changes to get rasterizer op to build externally.  PiperOrigin-RevId: 318294823

Stop returning NaN from cartesian_to_spherical_coordinates  For some inputs, z/radius returns values outside the range [-1, 1], which causes theta to be NaN.  This CL uses tf.clip_by_value to ensure that the ratio falls within range, which fixes the NaNs. It also stops gradients for out of range values, but since out-of-range values return NaN, no useful gradients could have been calculated anyway.  PiperOrigin-RevId: 327894713

Migrate tensorflow_graphics/geometry/transformation to using TensorFlow 2.  Following changes are made to the library code:  - tf.compat.v1.name_scope      -> tf.name_scope - tf.compat.v1.where.          -> tf.where - tf.compat.v1.assert_equal    -> tf.debugging.assert_equal - tf.compat.v1.dimension_value -> tf.compat.dimension_value  Following changes are made to the test code:  - Remove tf.compat.v1.get_variable() - Remove tf.compat.v1.global_variables_initializer() - Remove tf.compat.v1.Session() except for a couple of places using assert_jacobian_is_finite() that depends on TensorFlow v1 libraries  PiperOrigin-RevId: 356156516

Migrate tensorflow_graphics/util to using TensorFlow 2.  - tf.compat.v1.name_scope            -> tf.name_scope - tf.compat.v1.where                 -> tf.where - tf.compat.v1.dimension_value       -> tf.compat.dimension_value - tf.compat.v1.assert_*              -> tf.debugging.assert_* - tf.compat.v1.div                   -> tf.math.floordiv - tf.compat.v2.test.compute_gradient -> tf.test.compute_gradient  Don't replace:  - tf.compat.v1.Dimension, tf.compat.v1.test.compute_gradient, tf.compat.v1.set_random_seed, and tf.compat.v1.lite.TFLiteConverter.from_session as they don't have TensorFlow 2 equivalents  - tf.compat.v1.Session, tf.compat.v1.global_variables_initializer, compat.v1.placeholder, tf.compat.v1.placeholder_with_default, and tf.compat.v1.sparse.placeholder as they are required to run tests in graph mode  PiperOrigin-RevId: 369156735

Fix missing tensorflow_graphics documentation.  Several modules were missing documentation due to missing imports in the __init__.py files. I added the ones I could see that were missing. Trying to fix the inverse rendering colab.  Adding a trailing comma to the "provenance=[]" field in cl/389701407 to satisfy the presubmit also broke the JSON, because JSON doesn't allow trailing commas in the last item of a list. In this CL I moved provenance up in the list to avoid the trailing comma issue.  PiperOrigin-RevId: 392659258

[numpy] Fix users of NumPy APIs that are removed in NumPy 2.0.  This change migrates users of APIs removed in NumPy 2.0 to their recommended replacements (https://numpy.org/devdocs/numpy_2_0_migration_guide.html).  PiperOrigin-RevId: 655956468

[numpy] Fix users of NumPy APIs that are removed in NumPy 2.0.  This change migrates users of APIs removed in NumPy 2.0 to their recommended replacements (https://numpy.org/doc/stable/numpy_2_0_migration_guide.html).  This change replaces uses of `np.math`, which is a deprecated alias for the builtin `math` module, with the builtin `math` module. `np.math` is removed in NumPy 2.0.  PiperOrigin-RevId: 658227973
